{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775843458707,"sessionID":"ses_2877b76d4ffeKKOb4j15pM2jaz","part":{"id":"prt_d7884b9d30018gJw4SVsJZyCQH","messageID":"msg_d7884adb3001CNKhnPdE5Kz9OH","sessionID":"ses_2877b76d4ffeKKOb4j15pM2jaz","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_af4f418a8fd64eb78f5904d4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/workloadmanager/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/workloadmanager/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-005: Sandbox 创建处理器 (Sandbox Creation Processor)\n2: \n3: - **AR ID**: AR-005\n4: - **Module**: pkg/workloadmanager\n5: - **Language**: Go\n6: - **Size**: M\n7: - **Status**: ST-1 Completed\n8: \n9: ## 1. Architecture\n10: \n11: ### 1.1 Overview\n12: \n13: The WorkloadManager module provides a high-level abstraction layer for managing AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources in the agentcube system. It wraps the generated client-go library and exposes a clean interface for CRUD operations and watching resources.\n14: \n15: ### 1.2 Component Structure\n16: \n17: ```\n18: pkg/workloadmanager/\n19: ├── client.go          # Kubernetes client initialization\n20: ├── service.go         # WorkloadManager interface and implementation\n21: ├── server.go          # HTTP server for workload management API\n22: ├── types.go           # Request/Response types and error handling\n23: └── design.md          # This design document\n24: ```\n25: \n26: ### 1.3 Layered Architecture\n27: \n28: ```\n29: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐\n30: │            HTTP API Layer               │\n31: │           (server.go)                   │\n32: ├─────────────────────────────────────────┤\n33: │          Service Layer                  │\n34: │      (WorkloadManager interface)        │\n35: ├─────────────────────────────────────────┤\n36: │         Client Layer                    │\n37: │     (versioned.Interface wrapper)       │\n38: ├─────────────────────────────────────────┤\n39: │      Generated client-go                │\n40: │  github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go │\n41: └─────────────────────────────────────────┘\n42: ```\n43: \n44: ## 2. Data Structures\n45: \n46: ### 2.1 Core Types\n47: \n48: #### K8sClient\n49: ```go\n50: type K8sClient struct {\n51:     Clientset        versioned.Interface\n52:     DynamicClient    dynamic.Interface\n53:     KubernetesClient *kubernetes.Clientset\n54: }\n55: ```\n56: - **Purpose**: Holds all Kubernetes client instances\n57: - **Lifecycle**: Created on startup, closed on shutdown\n58: \n59: #### WorkloadManager Interface\n60: ```go\n61: type WorkloadManager interface {\n62:     // AgentRuntime operations\n63:     CreateAgentRuntime(ctx context.Context, namespace string, agentRuntime *agentcubev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, opts metav1.CreateOptions) (*agentcubev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n64:     GetAgentRuntime(ctx context.Context, namespace, name string, opts metav1.GetOptions) (*agentcubev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n65:     ListAgentRuntimes(ctx context.Context, namespace string, opts metav1.ListOptions) (*agentcubev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeList, error)\n66:     UpdateAgentRuntime(ctx context.Context, namespace string, agentRuntime *agentcubev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, opts metav1.UpdateOptions) (*agentcubev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n67:     DeleteAgentRuntime(ctx context.Context, namespace, name string, opts metav1.DeleteOptions) error\n68:     GetAgentRuntimeStatus(ctx context.Context, namespace, name string, opts metav1.GetOptions) (*agentcubev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeStatus, error)\n69:     PatchAgentRuntimeStatus(ctx context.Context, namespace, name string, pt types.PatchType, data []byte, opts metav1.PatchOptions) (*agentcubev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n70:     WatchAgentRuntimes(ctx context.Context, namespace string, opts metav1.ListOptions) (watch.Interface, error)\n71: \n72:     // CodeInterpreter operations\n73:     CreateCodeInterpreter(ctx context.Context, namespace string, codeInterpreter *agentcubev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, opts metav1.CreateOptions) (*agentcubev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, error)\n74:     GetCodeInterpreter(ctx context.Context, namespace, name string, opts metav1.GetOptions) (*agentcubev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, error)\n75:     ListCodeInterpreters(ctx context.Context, namespace string, opts metav1.ListOptions) (*agentcubev1alpha1.CodeInterpreterList, error)\n76:     UpdateCodeInterpreter(ctx context.Context, namespace string, codeInterpreter *agentcubev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, opts metav1.UpdateOptions) (*agentcubev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, error)\n77:     DeleteCodeInterpreter(ctx context.Context, namespace, name string, opts metav1.DeleteOptions) error\n78:     GetCodeInterpreterStatus(ctx context.Context, namespace, name string, opts metav1.GetOptions) (*agentcubev1alpha1.CodeInterpreterStatus, error)\n79:     PatchCodeInterpreterStatus(ctx context.Context, namespace, name string, pt types.PatchType, data []byte, opts metav1.PatchOptions) (*agentcubev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, error)\n80:     WatchCodeInterpreters(ctx context.Context, namespace string, opts metav1.ListOptions) (watch.Interface, error)\n81: \n82:     Close() error\n83: }\n84: ```\n85: \n86: ### 2.2 Request/Response Types\n87: \n88: | Type | File | Purpose |\n89: |------|------|---------|\n90: | APIResponse | types.go | Standard API response wrapper |\n91: | APIError | types.go | Standard error response |\n92: | ListMeta | types.go | Pagination metadata |\n93: | PaginationRequest | types.go | Query parameters for list operations |\n94: | AgentRuntimeListResponse | types.go | AgentRuntime list response |\n95: | CodeInterpreterListResponse | types.go | CodeInterpreter list response |\n96: | CreateAgentRuntimeRequest | types.go | AgentRuntime creation request |\n97: | CreateCodeInterpreterRequest | types.go | CodeInterpreter creation request |\n98: | WatchEvent | types.go | Watch event wrapper |\n99: \n100: ## 3. API Contracts\n101: \n102: ### 3.1 Client Initialization\n103: \n104: #### NewK8sClient\n105: ```go\n106: func NewK8sClient(kubeconfig string) (*K8sClient, error)\n107: ```\n108: - **Parameters**: \n109:   - `kubeconfig`: Path to kubeconfig file, or empty string for default, or \"in-cluster\" for in-cluster mode\n110: - **Returns**: Initialized K8sClient with all client instances\n111: - **Errors**: Configuration loading errors, client creation errors\n112: \n113: #### NewInClusterClient\n114: ```go\n115: func NewInClusterClient() (*K8sClient, error)\n116: ```\n117: - **Purpose**: Convenience method for in-cluster deployment\n118: - **Returns**: Client configured from service account\n119: \n120: ### 3.2 AgentRuntime Operations\n121: \n122: | Operation | Method | Resource Path |\n123: |-----------|--------|---------------|\n124: | Create | POST | /apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/namespaces/{namespace}/agentruntimes |\n125: | Get | GET | /apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/namespaces/{namespace}/agentruntimes/{name} |\n126: | List | GET | /apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/namespaces/{namespace}/agentruntimes |\n127: | Update | PUT | /apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/namespaces/{namespace}/agentruntimes/{name} |\n128: | Delete | DELETE | /apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/namespaces/{namespace}/agentruntimes/{name} |\n129: | Watch | GET (watch=true) | /apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/namespaces/{namespace}/agentruntimes?watch=true |\n130: | Patch Status | PATCH | /apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/namespaces/{namespace}/agentruntimes/{name}/status |\n131: \n132: ### 3.3 CodeInterpreter Operations\n133: \n134: Same REST paths as AgentRuntime, with resource name `codeinterpreters`.\n135: \n136: ### 3.4 Query Parameters\n137: \n138: | Parameter | Type | Description |\n139: |-----------|------|-------------|\n140: | labelSelector | string | Label selector for filtering |\n141: | fieldSelector | string | Field selector for filtering |\n142: | watch | bool | Enable watch mode |\n143: | timeoutSeconds | int64 | Timeout for watch/list operations |\n144: | limit | int64 | Limit number of results |\n145: | continue | string | Continue token for pagination |\n146: | resourceVersion | string | Resource version for read consistency |\n147: \n148: ## 4. Error Handling\n149: \n150: ### 4.1 Error Types\n151: \n152: | Error Code | Reason | Description |\n153: |------------|--------|-------------|\n154: | 400 | BadRequest | Invalid request format |\n155: | 404 | NotFound | Resource not found |\n156: | 409 | Conflict | Resource already exists |\n157: | 422 | Invalid | Validation failed |\n158: | 500 | InternalError | Server error |\n159: | 503 | ServiceUnavailable | Cluster unavailable |\n160: \n161: ### 4.2 Error Response Format\n162: \n163: ```json\n164: {\n165:   \"kind\": \"Status\",\n166:   \"apiVersion\": \"v1\",\n167:   \"status\": \"Failure\",\n168:   \"message\": \"resource not found\",\n169:   \"reason\": \"NotFound\",\n170:   \"code\": 404,\n171:   \"details\": {\n172:     \"name\": \"my-runtime\",\n173:     \"kind\": \"agentruntime\",\n174:     \"causes\": [\n175:       {\n176:         \"message\": \"AgentRuntime.agentcube.volcano.sh \\\"my-runtime\\\" not found\",\n177:         \"field\": \"metadata.name\"\n178:       }\n179:     ]\n180:   }\n181: }\n182: ```\n183: \n184: ### 4.3 Error Translation\n185: \n186: All Kubernetes API errors are wrapped with context and propagated to callers. Errors include:\n187: - Resource name and namespace in error message\n188: - Original error as wrapped cause\n189: - Appropriate HTTP status codes\n190: \n191: ## 5. Testing Strategy\n192: \n193: ### 5.1 Unit Tests\n194: \n195: #### Client Initialization Tests\n196: - Test kubeconfig loading from default path\n197: - Test in-cluster config loading\n198: - Test error handling for invalid kubeconfig\n199: - Test client creation failures\n200: \n201: #### Service Operation Tests\n202: - Test CRUD operations with mock client\n203: - Test error propagation from client layer\n204: - Test context cancellation handling\n205: \n206: ### 5.2 Integration Tests\n207: \n208: - Test against real Kubernetes cluster (optional)\n209: - Test with fake clientset for controlled environment\n210: - Test resource lifecycle (create → get → update → delete)\n211: \n212: ### 5.3 Fake Client Usage\n213: \n214: The generated fake clientset should be used for testing:\n215: \n216: ```go\n217: import (\n218:     fakeagentcube \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/client/clientset/versioned/fake\"\n219:     \"k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes/fake\"\n220: )\n221: \n222: func TestWorkloadManager(t *testing.T) {\n223:     client := fakeagentcube.NewSimpleClientset()\n224:     k8s := fake.NewSimpleClientset()\n225:     \n226:     wm := workloadmanager.NewWorkloadManager(client)\n227:     \n228:     // Test operations\n229:     ar, err := wm.CreateAgentRuntime(ctx, \"default\", agentRuntime, metav1.CreateOptions{})\n230:     // assertions...\n231: }\n232: ```\n233: \n234: ### 5.4 Test Coverage Targets\n235: \n236: | Component | Target Coverage |\n237: |-----------|-----------------|\n238: | client.go | 80% |\n239: | service.go | 85% |\n240: | types.go | 90% |\n241: | server.go | 75% |\n242: \n243: ## 6. Dependencies\n244: \n245: ### 6.1 Direct Dependencies\n246: \n247: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n248: |---------|---------|---------|\n249: | k8s.io/client-go | latest | Kubernetes client infrastructure |\n250: | k8s.io/apimachinery | latest | API types and utilities |\n251: | k8s.io/klog/v2 | latest | Logging |\n252: \n253: ### 6.2 Internal Dependencies\n254: \n255: | Module | Purpose |\n256: |--------|---------|\n257: | github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go | Generated client library |\n258: | github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1 | API types |\n259: \n260: ## 7. Configuration\n261: \n262: ### 7.1 Environment Variables\n263: \n264: | Variable | Default | Description |\n265: |----------|---------|-------------|\n266: | KUBECONFIG | ~/.kube/config | Path to kubeconfig |\n267: | IN_CLUSTER | false | Use in-cluster config |\n268: \n269: ### 7.2 Flags\n270: \n271: | Flag | Type | Default | Description |\n272: |------|------|---------|-------------|\n273: | kubeconfig | string | \"\" | Path to kubeconfig |\n274: | master | string | \"\" | Kubernetes API server |\n275: \n276: ## 8. Performance Considerations\n277: \n278: ### 8.1 Client Caching\n279: \n280: - Reuse client instances across requests\n281: - Client initialization is expensive; cache at module level\n282: \n283: ### 8.2 List Operations\n284: \n285: - Use pagination for large result sets\n286: - Set reasonable timeouts (default: 30s)\n287: \n288: ### 8.3 Watch Connections\n289: \n290: - Implement reconnection logic for watch operations\n291: - Set appropriate timeout values\n292: - Clean up watch connections on client close\n293: \n294: ## 9. Security\n295: \n296: ### 9.1 RBAC Requirements\n297: \n298: The WorkloadManager requires the following RBAC permissions:\n299: \n300: ```yaml\n301: rules:\n302: - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n303:   resources: [\"agentruntimes\", \"codeinterpreters\"]\n304:   verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n305: - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n306:   resources: [\"agentruntimes/status\", \"codeinterpreters/status\"]\n307:   verbs: [\"get\", \"update\", \"patch\"]\n308: ```\n309: \n310: ### 9.2 Credentials\n311: \n312: - Use service account credentials when running in-cluster\n313: - Support kubeconfig with arbitrary authentication methods\n314: - Never log or expose credentials\n315: \n316: ## 10. References\n317: \n318: - [client-go library](../deployment/client-go.md)\n319: - [Kubernetes API Conventions](https://git.k8s.io/community/contributors/devel/sig-architecture/api-conventions.md)\n320: - [code-generator usage](https://git.k8s.io/code-generator)\n\n(End of file - total 320 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-005: Sandbox 创建处理器 (Sandbox Creation Processor)\n\n- **AR ID**: AR-005\n- **Module**: pkg/workloadmanager\n- **Language**: Go\n- **Size**: M\n- **Status**: ST-1 Completed\n\n## 1. Architecture\n\n### 1.1 Overview\n\nThe WorkloadManager module provides a high-level abstraction layer for managing AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources in the agentcube system. It wraps the generated client-go library and exposes a clean interface for CRUD operations and watching resources.\n\n### 1.2 Component Structure\n\n```\npkg/workloadmanager/\n├── client.go          # Kubernetes client initialization\n├── service.go         # WorkloadManager interface and implementation","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/workloadmanager/design.md","time":{"start":1775843458687,"end":1775843458704}}}}
